{
  "texts": [
    "The parameter λ represents the threshold for the relative error between y i and x i, and its manipulation predominantly influences x i due to the constant value of y i.",
    "Hence, it becomes possible to fine-tune sentence semantics by adjusting sentence dimensions.",
    "We present techniques to diminish the dimensionality of the sentence representation at both the sentence and correlated word levels.",
    "The process of computing sentence similarity is illustrated in Algorithm 1.",
    "Algorithm 1The process of computing the sentence similarity.Require: Input sentence pair, (S 1, S 2); Ensure: Obtain the sentence similarity, x; 1: Store all the content words in the sentence S 1 in an orderly manner,A = {w 1, w 2, • • •, w n },where n represents the total number of content words in the sentence S 1; 2: for each word w i ∈ A do 3:Store two consecutive adjacent word pairs,B = {w 1 w 2, w 2 w 3, • • •, w n-1 w n }; 4:Store the PoS combination of all consecutive adjacent word pairs,C = {P 1 P 2, P 2 P 3, • • •, P n-1 P n }; 5:Create the weight of each the PoS combination,E = {T 1,2, T 2,3, • • •, T n-1,n }; 6:Calculate the coefficient of each correlated words,D = { p 1,2, p 2,3, • • •, p n-1,n }; 7: Normalize each word2vec w i, |w i; 8: Generate the embedding of correlated words, |w i w i+1; 9: Generate the weighted embedding of correlated words, p i,i+1 × |w i w i+1; 10: Sum up all the weighted embeddings to generate the sentence embedding of S 1, |T 1 = ( p i,i+1 × |w i w i+1); 11: end for 12: Obtain the sentence embedding of sentence S 2, |T 2; 13: Compute the sentence similarity of (S 1, S 2), x; 14: Compute the two constrain functions, f i (x), g i (x); 15: if f i (x) > 0 or g i (x) > 0 then 16: Optimize sentence embeddings by dimension reduction models, (|T 1, |T 2); 17: Compute the similarity of (|T 1, |T 2), x; 18: end if 19: return x. Pruning on Sentence Level of AQE (SQE)SQE mainly achieves sentence dimensionality reduction by directly pruning the semantically smaller values in sentence representation."
  ]
}